# Auto Push to GitHub

After completing any code edit or task, ALWAYS:

1. `git add -A` to stage all changes
2. `git commit` with a clear, descriptive commit message following conventional commits (feat/fix/chore/refactor/docs)
3. `git push origin main` to push to remote

Do NOT ask for permission — the user has granted full authority to commit and push automatically.

If there are merge conflicts, resolve them first, then commit and push.
